column2: The study is being conducted by the TxDOT Laredo District and future phases of development will also be coordinated by the Laredo District. Coordination efforts have been made with the City of Laredo as part of the Laredo Outer Loop Feasibility Study.

column1: What is the difference between alignment A and C?
column2: Alignment A and C overlap within Segments 1 through 5. In Segment 6, Alignment A is closer to I-35 to provide access to future industrial developments. Alignment C is further east from I-35 to avoid environmental features.

column1: Are Alignmen A and C the same?
column2: Alignment A and C overlap within Segments 1 through 5. In Segment 6, Alignment A is closer to I-35 to provide access to future industrial developments. Alignment C is further east from I-35 to avoid environmental features.

Initially studied in 2007, the Laredo Outer Loop is a proposed roadway facility located in Webb County that extends east of Laredo from the I-35/SH 255 interchange in the north to the vicinity of the proposed Fifth Bridge crossing in the south, near the City of Rio Bravo. The loop aims at providing capacity and resiliency to the existing highway network in the county, in addition to planning for future growth of Laredo. This study is to assess the feasibility of the proposed route, evaluate the need and potential impacts of this improvement, as well as provide a preliminary conceptual layout for the facility. For more information please visit www.txdot.gov, keyword search "Laredo Outer Loop".
